  "response": "Here are several good substitutes for rice wine vinegar:\n\n1. Apple cider vinegar\n- Similar acidity\n- Slightly fruity flavor\n- Works well in most recipes\n\n2. White wine vinegar\n- Mild, clean taste\n- Good all-purpose substitute\n- Similar acidity level\n\n3. White vinegar\n- More neutral flavor\n- Strongest substitution option\n- Dilute with water if too sharp\n\n4. Champagne vinegar\n- Lighter, more delicate flavor\n- Good for more subtle dishes\n\n5. Lemon or lime juice\n- Provides acidity\n- Adds fresh citrus notes\n- Works well in many Asian recipes\n\n6. Sherry vinegar\n- More complex flavor\n- Good for marinades and dressings\n\nWhen substituting, use the same amount of the alternative as you would rice wine vinegar. Each substitute will slightly change the dish's flavor profile, so choose based on your specific recipe and taste preferences.",
